# Main/View.elm — EARLY

The full view layer of the Elm client. One entry point (`view`)
that composes every visible element, plus the turn-ceremony
helpers that produce StatusMessage and PopupContent records.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Extracted 2026-04-19 from the pre-split
  `Main.elm` monolith. The biggest single chunk of the split —
  Main.elm was mostly HTML.
- **Stability:** The view *layer* is stable; individual styles
  and copy are tuned continuously.

## Public API

- `view : Model -> Html Msg` — the top-level view composition.
  Composes top bar, status bar, hand column, board column,
  drag overlay, and popup (last is suppressed during replay).
- `statusForCompleteTurn : Result err CompleteTurnOutcome ->
  StatusMessage` — maps turn results to status-bar text and
  colour kind. Used by the update function to write into
  `model.status`.
- `popupForCompleteTurn : Result err CompleteTurnOutcome ->
  Maybe PopupContent` — maps turn results to the ceremony
  popup content (admin character + body text). Used by the
  update function to write into `model.popup`.

## Visual structure

```
Html
├── viewTopBar            "Welcome to Lyn Rummy!" banner
├── viewStatusBar         per-status color + text
├── div (two-column flex)
│   ├── handColumn        turn # header + two viewPlayerRow
│   │   ├── viewPlayerRow P1
│   │   └── viewPlayerRow P2
│   │       └── viewTurnControls   (shown for the active row)
│   │           [ Complete turn / Hint / Replay / Lobby ]
│   └── boardColumn
│       └── boardWithWings
│           ├── viewStackForBoard (×N)
│           └── viewWingAt       (×M, during drag only)
├── draggedOverlay        floating drag card (fixed-position)
└── viewPopup             modal ceremony (suppressed in replay)
```

## Player row branch logic

`viewPlayerRow` renders name + score always, then branches on
`idx == model.activePlayerIndex`:

- **Active row** — `View.viewHandHeading` + `View.viewHand`
  with `Gesture.handCardAttrs` attrs (mousedown + dim + hint
  highlight) + `viewTurnControls`.
- **Inactive row** — just `"N cards"` text, no interaction.

## Turn-controls buttons (per row state)

| Situation | Buttons |
|---|---|
| Not replaying | Complete turn / Hint / Instant replay / Lobby |
| Replaying, not paused | Complete turn / Hint / Pause / Lobby |
| Replaying, paused | Complete turn / Hint / Resume / Lobby |

## Board rendering

- `boardColumn` wraps `View.viewBoardHeading` above `boardWithWings`.
- `boardWithWings` calls `View.boardShellWith [id boardDomId]`
  to produce the board frame (the `id` is what
  `Browser.Dom.getElement` resolves during drag).
- `boardChildren` = `stackNodes ++ wingNodes`. Wings appear
  only while dragging (from `info.wings`).
- `viewStackForBoard` hides the source stack when dragging it
  from the board (the floating overlay shows it instead);
  otherwise delegates to `View.viewStack` or
  `View.viewStackWithCardAttrs` (for non-drag: per-card
  mousedown to allow per-card click→split detection).
- `viewWingAt` computes the wing's left edge from the target
  stack's loc + width, paints `mergeableGreen` or
  `mergeableHover`, attaches WingEntered / WingLeft events.

## Popup rendering

`viewPopup` is modal via `z-index: 2000` + full-viewport
backdrop. Content: admin name in navy bold + body in pre-wrap +
single OK button. No ESC, no click-outside, no focus trap. The
popup is suppressed during replay per the
"suppress-popups-in-replay" UX decision.

## Ceremony character casting

`popupFromOutcome` picks the admin character based on result:

| Result | Admin | Tone |
|---|---|---|
| Failure | Angry Cat | "The board is not clean!" |
| SuccessButNeedsCards | Oliver | "Sorry you couldn't find a move." |
| SuccessAsVictor | Steve | "First person to play all their cards!" |
| SuccessWithHandEmptied | Steve | "You emptied your hand!" |
| Success | Steve | "The board is growing!" |

The three Successes all speak as Steve because they're the
positive cases. Angry Cat is the scold. Oliver is the
apologetic friend (when the player couldn't play anything).

## Drag overlay

`draggedOverlay` renders the floating element that tracks the
cursor during drag. Fixed-position, pointer-events disabled
(so wings underneath still respond), z-index 1000. Branches
on source type: `FromBoardStack` renders the full stack,
`FromHandCard` renders just the card with a white background.

## What this module deliberately does NOT do

- State transitions. Everything here is `_ -> Html Msg` or
  pure data functions.
- HTTP. Ceremony helpers produce records that `update` writes
  into Model; no calls.
- Gesture resolution. That's `Main.Gesture`. This module just
  attaches the mousedown events via `Gesture.handCardAttrs`
  and `Gesture.cardMouseDown`.

## Dependencies

- `Html`, `Html.Attributes`, `Html.Events` — standard view.
- `LynRummy.BoardActions` — `Side(..)` for wing placement.
- `LynRummy.CardStack` — `CardStack`, `stackPitch`,
  `stackDisplayWidth`.
- `LynRummy.Hand` — `Hand` type.
- `LynRummy.PlayerTurn` — `CompleteTurnResult(..)`.
- `LynRummy.View` — domain-level primitives: `viewStack`,
  `viewHand`, `viewWing`, `boardShellWith`, colour constants.
- `LynRummy.WingOracle` — `WingId` type.
- `Main.Gesture` — `handCardAttrs`, `cardMouseDown` for event
  wiring.
- `Main.Msg` — Msg constructors for onClick / onMouseEnter /
  onMouseLeave.
- `Main.State` — Model, PopupContent, StatusMessage + kind,
  DragState + info, boardDomId, activeHand.
